situation:
The section of a prestressed hollow core slab is shown. The slab is simply supported over a span of 7.5m and carries a superimposed dead load of 3kPa and live load of 5kPa. The total prestressing force is 1400kN at an eccentricity of 40mm. The properties of the section are as follows:
Cross-sectional area = 160x103mm2
Moment of inertia, Ix=350x106mm4
Unit weight of concrete = 23.5kN/m3

subquestions.question: Determine the stress at the bottom fibers at L/4 due to dead load.
Determine the stress at the top fibers at midspan due to the total load.
What maximum concentrated load can act at the midspan if the maximum allowable tensile stress in concrete is 3MPa and the maximum allowable compressive stress is 18MPa?
